I'm a firm believer in greasy food wrappers and napkins.  Put several twigs down to make it so air can get under it all, lay down a greasy napkin from last night's meal, a few more twigs and larger sticks, another greasy napkin or bag, and the rest of the wood in either a crosshatch pattern or a teepee.  It's like napalm.  It gets rid of litter, doesn't involve stinky petroleum, and even smells good.

Another great fire starter is a lint. You can find it in the corner of your pockets or if you have access to a dryer it’s smart to keep some in your backpack. You can mix it with petroleum jelly and it will stay waterproof that way!

An important note about using crumpled paper as your fire starter: make sure that you don’t crumple it too tightly. There needs to be plenty of space for airflow and the flames to actually catch!
